From Spenser Aden Subject Re diet for Crohn's IBD In article Stephen Holland writes In article John Eyles wrote A friend has what is apparently a fairly minor case of Crohn's But she can't seem to eat certain foods such as fresh vegetables without discomfort and of course she wants to avoid a Her question is are there any nutritionists who specialize in the problems of people with Crohn's disease If she is having problems with fresh vegetables the guess is that there is some obstruction of the Without knowing more it is not possible to say whether the obstruction is permanent due to scarring or temporary due to swelling of inflammed In general there are no dietary limitations in patients with Crohn's except as they relate to There is no evidence that any foods will bring on recurrence of Crohn' Interesting statements simply because I have been told I'm certainly not questioning Steve's claims as for one I am not a doctor and I agree that foods don't bring on the recurrence of Crohn' But inflammation can be either mildly or DRASTICALLY enhanced due to Having had one major obstruction resulting in resection is that a good enough caveat I was told that a LOW RESIDUE diet is called Basically the idea is that if there is inflammation of the gut which may not be realized by the patient any residue in the system can be caught in the folds of inflammation and constantly irritate thus exacerbating the Therefore anything that doesn't digest completely by the point of common inflammation should be With what I've been told is typical Crohn's of the terminal ileum my diet should be low residue consisting of Completely out never again items o corn kernel husk doesn't digest most of us know this o popcorn same o dried dehydrated fruit and fruit skins o nuts Very tough when it comes to giving up some fudge Discouraged greatly o raw vegetables too fibrous o wheat and raw grain breads o exotic lettuce iceberg is ok since it's apparently mostly water o greens turnip mustard kale o little seeds like sesame try getting an Arby's without it o long grain and wild rice husky o beans you'll generate enough gas alone without them o BASICALLY anything that requires heavy digestive processing I was told that the more processed the food the better rather ironic in this day and age The whole point is PREVENTATIVE you want to give your system as little chance to inflame as I was told that among the NUMEROUS things that were heavily discouraged I only listed a few to try the ones I wanted and see how I If it's bad don't do it again Remember though that this was while I was in For Veggies cook the daylights out of I prefer steaming I think it's cooks more thoroughly you're mileage may As with anything else CHECK WITH YOUR Don't just take my But this is the info I've been given and it may be a starting point for Good luck Spenser Spenser Aden Lockheed Engineering and Sciences NASA Flight Data and Evaluation Office Johnson Space Center Houston Internet Opinions herein are mine if above bounces Eschew unknown